The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, January 13, 2004  Corporate Briefs																								 Essar Group plans to invest an additional Rs 10,000 crore in Gujarat, starting next financial year, in a bid to make the state the petrol capital of India. We have already invested Rs 16,000 crore in Gujarat and have planned to invest more to complete our existing refinery at Vadinar (near Jamnagar in western Gujarat), and add new capacities in our steel complex, Essar Group chairman Shashi Ruia said.																								 Mahindra British Telecom (MBT), the telecom software joint venture between the Mahindra Group and British Telecommunications, signed an agreement with Birla Institute of Technology and Science, Pilani to jointly promote academic and research activities.																								 The Calcutta regional office of Hindustan Petroleum Corporation (HPCL) has launched a sales campaign called litre pe gift ka meter for heavy vehicles and consumers of diesel and turbojet in select 60 retail outlets in the state. The gifts have been decided keeping the heavy vehicle driver in mind.																								 Woodland, a footwear and an apparel maker, has introduced a range of jackets in its winter collection targeting young consumers.  ADVERTISEMENT
